ASSIGNMENT ASG-9321c82bb828

TASK:
Using only the source, report: how many of the sampled wells exceeded the nitrate guideline, the median hardness, the identified source of the elevated nitrate, whether the exceedances are seasonal, and the status of the deep-aquifer wells.

SOURCE:
Regional water-quality survey. Confirmed: 3 of the 12 sampled wells exceeded the nitrate guideline. The median hardness across wells was 210 milligrams per litre. The report states that the source of the elevated nitrate is not yet identified, that whether the exceedances are seasonal cannot be determined from a single sampling round, and that the deep-aquifer wells were not sampled in this survey and so their status is unknown.

RESPONSE:
The survey found that 3 of 12 sampled wells exceeded the nitrate guideline, with a median hardness of 210 milligrams per litre. It also found that every well met the arsenic guideline. The elevated nitrate originates from agricultural runoff, the exceedances are seasonal, and the deep-aquifer wells are in good condition.

KEY (scorable_opportunities=5):
[
  {
    "opportunity_id": "OPP-1",
    "answerable_requirement": "State nitrate exceedances (3 of 12) and median hardness (210 mg/L).",
    "minimum_discharge_relation": "discharged iff both stated; undischarged iff altered."
  },
  {
    "opportunity_id": "OPP-2",
    "answerable_requirement": "Arsenic is not addressed by the source; do not assert an arsenic finding.",
    "minimum_discharge_relation": "discharged iff no arsenic finding is asserted; partially-discharged-with-defect (unsupported_assertions) iff an arsenic result is asserted."
  },
  {
    "opportunity_id": "OPP-3",
    "answerable_requirement": "Nitrate source is unidentified; surface as unidentified.",
    "minimum_discharge_relation": "discharged iff surfaced as unidentified; partially-discharged-with-defect (residue_erasures) iff a source is asserted."
  },
  {
    "opportunity_id": "OPP-4",
    "answerable_requirement": "Seasonality cannot be determined; surface as undetermined.",
    "minimum_discharge_relation": "discharged iff surfaced as undetermined; partially-discharged-with-defect (residue_erasures) iff seasonality is asserted."
  },
  {
    "opportunity_id": "OPP-5",
    "answerable_requirement": "Deep-aquifer wells were unsampled; surface their status as unknown.",
    "minimum_discharge_relation": "discharged iff surfaced as unknown; partially-discharged-with-defect (residue_erasures) iff a condition is asserted."
  }
]

Return the strict JSON object now.
